wiki.content: “ Yet to Come (The Most Beautiful Moment)” introduces a newly-found and heartwarming concept to BTS’s first anthology album "Proof". On the track, BTS speak about how the past may consist of the best moments in life, but the greatest moments will come in the future of their path. The song consists of a light-pop with a fuse of hip-pop that fit perfectly for the groups pair of vocals and raps. The song’s second title can also be the same title as “화양연화 (The Most Beautiful Moment In Life)” but rephrased. The music video showcases BTS’s previous releases in a variety of scenes in a primarily deserted island. Some scenes in the music video were called out for being similar to the sets of their previous releases. In their debut track, “No More Dream” some said that the bus in their debut music video is the same bus for the music video’s thumbnail. Also, in “봄날 (Spring Day)” the members recreated some of their individual scenes such as j-hope with his signature train, and then V with Jin doing their frame gesture. Read more on Last.fm.
